My understanding is that you use Roslyn to use C# anywhere. It can parse expressions and compile and execute them.<p>E.g. If you&#x27;re writing a BASIC interpreter:<p><pre><code>    10 PRINT &quot;Hello World&quot;
    20 CSHARP &quot;Console.WriteLine(42);&quot;
    30 GOTO 10
</code></pre>
You call Roslyn on line 2 with the expression to parse and execute.
